cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COM, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper analyzes the frame error rate (FER) of the hybrid relay selection (HRS) scheme in wireless relay networks, which involves information theory concepts such as signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) and error control coding. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on cooperative wireless systems and relay networks, which are relevant to the networking and internet architecture subfield. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The HRS scheme involves adaptive selection of amplify-and-forward (AF) and decode-and-forward (DF) protocols based on decoding results, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.COM (Computational Complexity): The paper does not explicitly address computational complexity, but the analysis of FER expressions and asymptotic behavior may involve computational complexity considerations. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper does not focus on multimedia specifically, but the analysis of wireless relay networks may have implications for multimedia applications.
